"Anon" MCs are a meme of sorts; it's a cultural affiliation thing. Like other thread-localized memes, it demonstrates belonging and some degree of commitment to the subject matter in that particular story. The reason named anons come off cringy is because they're scarce, so the use of one looks a lot more pretentious than it might under normal circumstances.

I like it, personally. Traditions are important to communities, especially in ones where our identity would otherwise be unclear. They're also just kind of fun.

Pretty much, yeah. I visualize a lot of my Anons as the kind of silent protagonist sort you see a lot in games, kind of like Link I suppose.
